  <original-body>This patch fixes the http_basic_auth with long credentials.

A long username/password results in a (base64 encoded) request header string that contains newlines (\n). When decoding, Rails splitted the header with &quot;split()&quot; and used only the last part of the result. With the patch it splits it in max. two parts &quot;split(' ', 2)&quot;.</original-body>
